Raspberry pi 4 connect with I2C LCD


#Create a new Python script:
nano lcd_test.py

Install virtual environment
sudo apt install python3-venv -y

Create a new virtual environment:
python3 -m venv lcd_env

Activate the virtual environment:
source lcd_env/bin/activate

Install rpi_lcd inside the virtual environment:
pip install rpi_lcd

Run your script inside the virtual environment:
python lcd_test.py

Deactivate the virtual environment when done:
deactivate



##Code

from rpi_lcd import LCD
import time

lcd = LCD()

try:
    lcd.text("Hello, Raspberry!", 1)  # Line 1
    lcd.text("I2C LCD Working!", 2)   # Line 2
    time.sleep(5)  # Wait 5 seconds to see the text
    lcd.clear()  # Clear the LCD
except KeyboardInterrupt:
    lcd.clear()
